input.content:
Updating the Task #7 design spec based on Heydon's a11y review. Two changes:

**Change 1: Visible label for the add-todo input.** US-5 says "Input has a visible `<label>`" so we keep it visible, not visually hidden.

**Change 2: Real `<input type="checkbox">` instead of a button for todo completion.** Native checkbox gives us proper semantics ("Buy groceries, checkbox, not checked") and `aria-checked` for free.

Updated HTML structure for the todo list page:

```html
<!-- Add todo form -->
<form method="post" action="/todos" class="todo-add">
    <label for="new-todo" class="todo-add__label">New todo</label>
    <div class="todo-add__row">
        <input
            type="text"
            id="new-todo"
            name="title"
            placeholder="What do you need to do?"
            maxlength="300"
            autocomplete="off"
            class="todo-add__input"
        >
        <button type="submit" class="todo-add__button">Add</button>
    </div>
</form>

<!-- Todo list -->
{% if todos.is_empty() %}
<p class="todo-empty">No todos yet.</p>
{% else %}
<ul class="todo-list" role="list">
    {% for todo in todos %}
    <li class="todo-item {% if todo.completed %}todo-item--completed{% endif %}">
        <form method="post" action="/todos/{{ todo.id }}/toggle" class="todo-item__toggle">
            <input type="checkbox"
                   id="todo-{{ todo.id }}"
                   name="completed"
                   {% if todo.completed %}checked{% endif %}
            >
            <label for="todo-{{ todo.id }}" class="todo-item__title">{{ todo.title }}</label>
            <button type="submit" class="visually-hidden">Update</button>
        </form>
    </li>
    {% endfor %}
</ul>
{% endif %}
```

Updated CSS adjustments:

```css
/* Add form -- label above, input+button row below */
.todo-add {
  margin-block: var(--space-lg);
}

.todo-add__label {
  display: block;
  font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
  font-weight: var(--font-medium);
  margin-block-end: var(--space-xs);
}

.todo-add__row {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--space-sm);
}

.todo-add__input {
  flex: 1;
}

.todo-add__button {
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

/* Checkbox styling -- hide native, custom visual */
.todo-item__toggle input[type="checkbox"] {
  appearance: none;
  -webkit-appearance: none;
  inline-size: 1.25rem;
  block-size: 1.25rem;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  border: 2px solid var(--color-border-strong);
  border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  background: var(--color-bg-raised);
  cursor: pointer;
  margin: 0;
}

.todo-item__toggle input[type="checkbox"]:checked {
  background-color: var(--color-primary);
  border-color: var(--color-primary);
  /* Checkmark via background-image SVG */
  background-image: url("data:image/svg+xml,...");
  background-size: 0.75rem;
  background-position: center;
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
}
```

The checkbox `<label>` doubles as the todo title -- clicking the title text also toggles the checkbox. This is standard form behavior and feels natural in a todo list.

No-JS baseline: the hidden submit button lets users check/uncheck and submit the form. HTMX enhancement: `hx-post` on the checkbox replaces the form submission with an inline swap.

